<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Gaze1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Gaze,</orth> subst. 1) intent regard, look of eagerness or wonder: <bibl n="shak. ven 632" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 632</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lc 26" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 193" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 193</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 2.247" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL II, 247</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 5.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.226" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 1, 226</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.2.78" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 2, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.282" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 5, 282</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.3.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 3, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.3.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 3, 33</bibl>. <emph>to stand at g.</emph> == to stare: <bibl n="shak. luc 1149" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1149</bibl>.<lb />2) an object eagerly looked on: <cit><quote>the lovely g. where every eye doth dwell,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 5.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 5, 2</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>live to be the show and g. of the time,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 5.8.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 8, 24</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>